bib_record.title: Thermal neutron capture cross sections of the palladium isotopes

free_txt: Prompt gamma rays from the target were measured
with an n-type high-purity, 25% efficient, germanium
located 23.5 cm from the target. The detector is
Compton suppressed by a bismuth germanate
In the article an entirely new
method for the measurement of the total thermal radia-
tive cross sections sigma(0) was described and used.
Statistical model calculations with the Monte
Carlo computer code DICEBOX were performed to generate
simulated neutron capture decay schemes in order to
determine continuum cross section contribution feeding
